channel.description:
[b]Purpose[/b]: To teach you how to change your chatbox text color

[b]Difficulty[/b]: 1/10

[b]Assumed Knowledge[/b]: How to follow simple directions

[b]Classes Modified[/b]: client.java

[b]Step 1[/b]:

Open your client.java find this

[code]
                            class30_sub2_sub1_sub4.method385(0, s1 + ":", i1, 822, j1);
                            j1 += class30_sub2_sub1_sub4.method383(anInt1116, s1) + 8;
                            class30_sub2_sub1_sub4.method385(255, aStringArray944[k], i1, 822, j1);
[/code]

now, where it says "method385([b]0[/b], s1 + ":", i1, 822, j1);"
and "method385([b]225[/b], aStringArray944[k], i1, 822, j1);" 

Changing these numbers will change the color of the text [b]after[/b] sending the chat. The first one (0) will change the color of your name (example: "[b]xx nub xx:[/b] whats up")

and the second number (225) will change the actual text [b]after[/b] sending the chat (example: "xx nub xx: [b]whats up[/b]").


[b]Step 2[/b]:

A little ways down from the first bit of code, you will find this

[code]
            class30_sub2_sub1_sub4.method385(0, s + ":", 90, 822, 4);
            class30_sub2_sub1_sub4.method385(255, aString887 + "*", 90, 822, 6 + class30_sub2_sub1_sub4.method383(anInt1116, s + ": "));
            Class30_Sub2_Sub1.method339(77, 0, 479, 0, (byte)4);
[/code]

Just like you did before, this bit of code: "method385([b]0[/b], s1 + ":", i1, 822, k1);"

will change the color of your name [b]before[/b] sending the chat (example: "[b]xx nub xx:[/b] I am about to type this!").

and this code: "method385([b]255[/b], aStringArray944[k], i1, 822, k1);"

will change the color of the text [b]before[/b] sending the chat (example: "xx nub xx: [b]I am about to type this![/b]").

Here is a picture to give you an example:

[IMG]http://i134.photobucket.com/albums/q114/woot_019/chatcolor.jpg[/img]

Congrats you have changed your client's chatbox colors

Here is a list of the colors you can use:

